University of California at Berkeley. OK, it was part of a play,
``The Resistible Rise of Arturo Ui,'' by Bertolt Brecht, in the
first-ever American appearance by Brecht's own company, the
Berliner Ensemble. (And it was Berkeley.) Still, it was a little
startling, even for a visitor to the Bay Area bent on attending a
number of events, each of which, in its way, was attracting
attention for the disjointed cultural elements it brought together.
By Bruce Weber.
