Brookings Institution. ``It's usually cheaper and easier for
someone who's creative to fool a sensor.''
</P>
<P>
   And with U.S. commanders relying more on remote sensors and
long-distance weapons to pinpoint targets and spare pilot
casualties, the likelihood remains that even the best pilots and
most advanced missiles will get duped every now and then.
</P>
</TEXT>
