than Mayor Rudolph Giuliani, who was tickled by Edwin's spunkiness.
Edwin, after all, did what many have done before him: He came to
America to reinvent himself.
</P>
<P>
   _ By SUSAN SACHS
</P>
<P>
   Vodka and Water, a Deadly Mix
</P>
<P>
   Vodka is Russian for ``little water,'' a playful diminutive
ludicrously out of place given what it does to those who drink it
before taking a swim. In Moscow alone, 144 swimmers drowned between
