 &HT;    The Cox News Service spot sports budget for Tuesday, July 6,
1999.
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Photo and graphics information and editors' names can be found
at the end of this budget.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-MARLINS _ ATLANTA _ Braves vs. Florida Marlins game
coverage. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: First pitch is at 7:40 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-MARLINS _ ATLANTA _Braves notebook. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   BOXING
</P>
<P>
   BOX-HOLYFIELD _ Evander Holyfield begins preliminary training
Monday for a faceless opponent. He hopes it's Lennox Lewis, but the
boxing gods may pit him against someone else. Holyfield updates his
divorce proceedings, talks about life after revelations of
out-of-wedlock kids and says he wants to fight five more times
before retiring with a world tour. (Bunn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 40.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: WITH PHOTO (Holyfield's Fourth of July party).
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
   SOC-US-CHINA _ Women's world cup story, looking ahead to how the
U.S. will handle the rapidly improving China squad. (Parker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
