<P>
   KOSOVO-RUSSIA (Washington) _ NATO and Russian military
commanders resolved their differences over Russia's role in the
peacekeeping operation in Kosovo today, clearing the way for 3,600
Russian troops to arrive in the province after more than two weeks
of wrangling over details of the deployment. By Steven Lee Myers
with Michael Wines in Moscow.
