 &HT;    1ST UPDATE
 &HT;    EDs: Adds: JEB-BUSH
 &HT;    
 &HT;    The Cox News Service spot news budget for Tuesday, July 6, 1999.
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Photo and graphics information and editors' names can be found
at the end of this budget.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   JEB-BUSH _ Six months after taking office, Jeb Bush, whether or
not you agree with his policies, has proven to be an activist
governor who makes quick decisions and works at a pace that is
exhausting his mostly young staff. So far, Bush has gotten his way
on almost everything he wants politically but his office is still
struggling to meet the day-to-day demands of operating the
governor's office. (Crowley, Palm Beach Post). 30
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   LANGUAGE _ WASHINGTON _ The same biological force that
scientists believe drove the evolution of life could account for
the development of complex languages in humans, two Princeton
University scientists suggested Monday. A family that developed a
word for ``leopard'' would be more likely to survive - and pass the
word on to future generations - than a family that had not.
(Nesmith, Cox News Service). 23. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
<P>
   Spot news budgets move daily at 2 p.m. and 6 p.m. Eastern.
Additionally, separate features and commentary budgets move at 10
a.m., and sports and business budgets at 6 p.m. Additional updates
are possible if news developments warrant.
</P>
<P>
   All times are Eastern unless otherwise noted. If stories will
move after 8 p.m., an ETA will be given.
</P>
