SOC-CROUSE-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Is it a genuine enthusiasm for
the U.S. women's soccer team, or is it a staged event? When the
team arrived at LAX Monday, World Cup organizers had a group of
people there that looked more like a studio audience than soccer
supporters. 
By Karen Crouse. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBO-FRINGE (Los Angeles) _ Feature on baseball's fringe players.
Being the 25th man on a baseball team is tough enough because you
don't get regular playing time. But the threat of not having a job
next week is something that is very hard to deal with. 
By Steve Dilbeck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
