<HEADLINE>
BY DESIGN: MORE EXPOSURE FOR SANDALS  
 (HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Gwyneth Paltrow has been seen around town wearing
flip-flops, giving an imprimatur of sorts to bare flat sandals for
the city. Most people will probably reserve them for the beach or
country, but, hey, there are no rules anymore. Even men have taken
to wearing sandals, though of a sturdier style, with their city
clothes.
</P>
<P>
   Barneys New York has men's sandals with crossover fronts, by Miu
Miu ($235), and with slides, by Costume National ($210) and Tsubo
($95).
</P>
<P>
   The store's women's flat sandals include ankle ties, by
Freelance ($160) and Jutta Neumann ($210), and thongs, by Farrutx
($130 to $150), Rose's Roses ($195) and Freelance ($125).
</P>
<P>
   Flat thong sandals for women at Saks Fifth Avenue include one by
Studio Via Spiga ($88), a braided style by Salvatore Ferragamo
($175), one with braided gold cord by Yves Saint Laurent ($190),
and two costly whimsies by Gucci: with Indian beadwork ($460) and
with turquoise feathers ($350).
</P>
</TEXT>
